Police are keeping a close eye on a group of demonstrators along the N2 highway. CAPE TOWN - Police are keeping a close eye on a group of demonstrators along the N2 highway.Officials say the suspected service delivery protests flared up near Borcherds Quarry Road on Friday afternoon.Western Cape Traffic chief Kenny Africa says: Currently we ve got a situation on the N2 at Borcherds Quarry, where people are protesting. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)